        "title": "The Cortisol Connection",
        "caption": "FIG 1.0 — THE CANVAS",
        "body_text": "<p>It starts with a receptor in your eye called the melanopsin ganglion cell. This receptor is not interested in vision; it is interested in time. When it detects high-intensity, blue-spectrum light from above (the angle of the sun at noon), it suppresses melatonin and spikes cortisol.</p>",
